7:12, 2 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 08:35, 9 December 2018 (UTC) }} '''David Petrus Wenceslaus Henri Pröpper''' (born 2 September 1991) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for English {{English football updater|Brigh&HA}} club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].
==Club career== ===Early career=== Pröpper made his [[Eredivisie]] debut for [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on 17 January 2010 in a match against [[N.E.C. (football club)|NEC]] at [[Stadion de Goffert]], coming on as a substitute for [[Kevin van Diermen]] in the 84th minute.<ref name=Soccerway/> He made his first appearance in the starting line-up on 13 April 2010, in a match against [[NAC Breda]] at the [[GelreDome]].<ref name=Soccerway/> Pröpper made 11 appearances in the Eredivisie in the [[2009–10 Eredivisie|2009–10 season]].<ref name=Soccerway/>
In his second season at Vitesse he scored his first goal for the club, opening an eventual 2–4 defeat to [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]].{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
On 8 December 2015, he scored the winning goal for [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] against [[CSKA Moscow]] in the UEFA Champions League, ensuring a spot in the last 16 for PSV for the first time in nine years.{{citation needed|date=August 2017}}
===Brighton & Hove Albion=== On 7 August 2017, Pröpper signed for newly promoted [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on a four-year contract, for a club-record transfer fee.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40852639 |title=Davy Propper joins Brighton from PSV Eindhoven in record transfer |publisher=BBC Sport |date=7 August 2017 |accessdate=7 August 2017}}</ref> Propper scored his first goal for Brighton in a 2-1 Premier League away defeat to [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester]] on 26 February 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/search?client=ms-android-hmd-rev2&ei=Bsh6XKiaLumU1fAPkf6n2AM&q=leicestwr+v+brighton+&oq=leicestwr+v+brighton+&gs_l=mobile-gws-wiz-serp.3..35i304i39j0i13l4.64306.64661..66734...0.0..0.157.726.2j4......0....1.........0i71.em-bmWNClZc#sie=m;/g/11f67fnn1l;2;/m/02_tc;dt;fp;1;;|title=Leicester City V Brighton|date= 26 February 2019|accessdate= 26 February 2019}}</ref>
==International career== Pröpper has represented the [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|Netherlands U-19]] team in the qualification rounds for the [[2010 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]]. On 14 November 2009, Pröpper made his debut for the U-19 Oranje in a qualification match against [[Cyprus national under-19 football team|Cyprus]], coming on as a substitute for [[Steven Berghuis]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/under19/matches/season=2010/round=15351/match=304733/index.html |title=Under-19 2010 – Netherlands-Cyprus |publisher=UEFA |date=12 November 2009 |accessdate=26 May 2010}}</ref> On 17 November 2009, Pröpper was in the starting line-up and played the whole game in a match against [[Czech Republic national under-19 football team|Czech Republic]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://en.uefa.com/under19/matches/season=2010/round=15351/match=304759/index.html |title=Under-19 2010 – Czech Republic-Netherlands |publisher=UEFA |date=13 November 2009 |accessdate=26 May 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100610221308/http://en.uefa.com/under19/matches/season%3D2010/round%3D15351/match%3D304759/index.html |archivedate=10 June 2010 |df= }}</ref>
He made his [[Netherlands national football team|senior]] debut on 5 June 2015, replacing [[Captain (association football)|captain]] [[Robin van Persie]] in the 57th minute of an eventual 3–4 friendly defeat to the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] at the [[Johan Cruyff Arena|Amsterdam Arena]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Hill |first=Tim |title=USA produced an incredible comeback from 3–1 down to defeat Guus Hiddink's side at the Amsterdam Arena |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2015/jun/05/holland-usa-soccer-international-friendly-live |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |date=5 June 2015 |accessdate=5 June 2015}}</ref>
